1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,169
It's an excellent way to move your spirit.
2
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:08,290
Now is the magic word of success.
3
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:17,010
Tomorrow, next week, later, sometime, someday, often as not are synonyms for the failure word, never.
4
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:22,370
Lots of good dreams never come true because we say, I'll start someday,
5
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:26,209
when we should say, I'll start now, right now.
6
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,730
Take one example, saving money.
7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,209
Just about everybody agrees that saving money is a good idea.
8
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:41,810
But just because it's a good idea doesn't mean many folks follow an organized savings and investment program.
9
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:48,370
Many people have intentions to save, but only relatively few act on these intentions.
10
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:54,689
Here's how one young couple got into gear with a regular wealth-accumulation program.
11
00:00:55,120 --> 00:01:03,330
Bill's take-home income was $1,000 a month, but he and his wife Janet spent $1,000 each month too.
12
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:09,250
Both wanted to save, but there were always reasons why they felt they couldn't begin.
13
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:13,969
For years, they had promised themselves, we'll start when we get a raise,
14
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:18,050
when we've caught up with our installments, when we're over the hump,
15
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:20,290
next month, next year.
16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:24,929
Finally, Janet got disgusted with their failure to save.
17
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:28,850
She said to Bill, look, do we want to save or don't we?
18
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:35,169
He replied, of course we do, but you know as well as I we can't put aside anything now.
19
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,330
But for once, Janet was in a do-or-die mood.
20
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:44,050
We've been telling ourselves for years we're going to start a savings program.
21
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,090
We don't save because we think we can't.
22
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,250
Now let's start thinking we can.
23
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:53,890
I saw an ad today that shows if we'd save just $100 a month,
24
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:01,250
in 15 years we'd have $18,000 plus $6,600 accumulated interest.
25
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:09,730
The ad also said it's easier to spend what's left over after savings than it is to save what's left over after spending.
26
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:15,250
If you're game, let's start with 10% of your pay and let's save off the top.
27
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:20,290
We may eat crackers and milk before the month's up, but if we have to, we will.
28
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:26,610
Bill and Janet were cramped for a few months, but soon they were adjusted to their new budget.
29
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:33,810
Now they feel it's just as much fun to spend money on savings as it is to spend it on something else.
30
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,610
Want to write a note to a friend?
31
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,810
Do it now.
32
00:02:37,999 --> 00:02:40,610
Got an idea you think would help your business?
33
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:41,890
Present it now.
34
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:44,689
Live the advice of Benjamin Franklin.
35
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:48,370
Don't put off until tomorrow what you can do today.
36
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:59,010
Remember, thinking in terms of now gets things accomplished, but thinking in terms of someday or sometime usually means failure.
